# TypeScript Type Safety (TSX)

## Array Transformations with Conditional Filtering

When building arrays where some items should be conditionally excluded, use `flatMap` with empty array returns instead of `map` + `filter(Boolean)`. TypeScript cannot narrow types through `.filter(Boolean)`.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const items = list.map(x => condition(x) ? transform(x) : null).filter(Boolean)

// ✅ GOOD
const items = list.flatMap(x => condition(x) ? [transform(x)] : [])
```

## Avoid Non-null Assertions

Do not use `!` to silence type errors. Use proper guards or early returns.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const el = arr.find(x => x.id === id)!

// ✅ GOOD
const el = arr.find(x => x.id === id)
if (!el) return null
```
